docs.abstract: Some of what we saw was people cosplaying consciousness — symbolism that cost nothing and shifted no power.
docs.snippet: Some of what we saw was people cosplaying consciousness — symbolism that cost nothing and shifted no power.
docs.lead_paragraph: We are in a period of post-mortem reflection following the time during which racial justice protests were at their most intense. We now must ask ourselves: What has changed and what hasn’t? Have power and privilege truly been disrupted? Has oppression been alleviated? What will be the legacy of this moment?

docs.abstract: Many theater companies are closed, but that doesn’t mean you can’t immerse yourself in the magic of a play.
docs.snippet: Many theater companies are closed, but that doesn’t mean you can’t immerse yourself in the magic of a play.
docs.lead_paragraph: In the United States, stages mostly remain dark. But there is another option for finding that full immersion into the magic of the theater, and that’s through podcasts. These shows, available on most listening apps, will challenge the assumption that you need to be in a theater seat to be transported into another world.

headline.main: 5 Podcasts to Bring Theater Into Your Home

docs.abstract: A man affiliated with a right-wing group was shot and killed Saturday night. A caravan of supporters of President Trump had driven into downtown Portland.
docs.snippet: A man affiliated with a right-wing group was shot and killed Saturday night. A caravan of supporters of President Trump had driven into downtown Portland.
docs.lead_paragraph: PORTLAND, Ore. — A fatal shooting during a night of political conflict in Portland, Ore., has yet again escalated tensions in the city and further inflamed the issues of crime, protest and race that President Trump is trying to make a focus of presidential politics.

headline.main: One Person Dead in Portland After Clashes Between Trump Supporters and Protesters

docs.abstract: A backstage fixture at Democratic conventions, she helped speakers work with the teleprompter, read the audience and sharpen their message.
docs.snippet: A backstage fixture at Democratic conventions, she helped speakers work with the teleprompter, read the audience and sharpen their message.
docs.lead_paragraph: Christine Jahnke, a communications coach who prepared Democratic women to run for office and helped others, including Michelle Obama early in her White House years, become comfortable with public speaking, died on Aug. 4, her birthday, at her home in Washington. She was 57.

headline.main: Christine Jahnke, Speech Coach for Women in Politics, Dies at 57
headline.print_headline: Christine Jahnke, Speech Coach  For Women in Politics, Dies at 57

docs.abstract: In Kamala Harris, many women of color see a successful vice-presidential candidate standing atop a mountain of firsts — but also facing a gender and racial minefield.
docs.snippet: In Kamala Harris, many women of color see a successful vice-presidential candidate standing atop a mountain of firsts — but also facing a gender and racial minefield.
docs.lead_paragraph: HOLLYWOOD, Fla. — To Krystina François, a Haitian-American executive director of a Miami nonprofit organization, Kamala Harris is a lot like her, a first-generation daughter of immigrants pursuing the American dream.

headline.main: ‘Finally the Country Sees Us’: Some Women of Color Cheer Harris’s Rise

docs.abstract: As an Indian-American professor of African-American history, I am experiencing Biden’s vice-presidential pick as a personal gift.

docs.lead_paragraph: When I arrived in the United States in 1984, an Indian graduate student wanting to study African-American history, I was an anomaly. Most of my fellow South Asians were in STEM doctoral programs.

headline.print_headline: Biden Just Gave a Gift to Indian-Americans Like Me
